===========================
SQL construct consideration
===========================

Tables: Column Name, Data Type, Description and Constraints

sites
├── site_id (PK)
├── name
├── address
├── city
├── state
├── postal_code
├── country
├── latitude
├── longitude
├── elevation
├── area
├── timezone
├── weather_station_id (FK)
├── year_built
├── primary_function
└── custom_data (JSONB)
    ├── equipType
    └── elecFreq

equipment
├── equipment_id (PK)
├── site_id (FK)
├── name
├── parent_equipment_id (FK)
├── space_ref
├── equipment_type
├── hot_water_system_id (FK)
├── chilled_water_system_id (FK)
└── custom_data (JSONB)
    ├── designSource
    ├── designHotWaterPower
    ├── designMake
    ├── designModel
    └── designChilledWaterPower

points
├── point_id (PK)
├── equipment_id (FK)
├── site_id (FK)
├── name
├── data_type
├── point_type
├── unit
├── timezone
├── measurement_type
└── custom_data (JSONB)
    ├── predictionConf
    ├── sourcePointName
    ├── dataSyncRecovered
    ├── inScope
    ├── backgroundPoint
    ├── precision
    ├── dataSyncDownSince
    ├── dataSyncType
    ├── pointType
    ├── max
    ├── min
    ├── firingRate
    ├── act
    ├── capacity
    ├── lockout
    ├── offlineMeter
    └── dateCreated

BACnet Data
├── device_id (PK)
├── object_name
├── object_type (always "device")
├── vendor_name
├── vendor_identifier
├── model_name
├── firmware_revision
├── application_software_version
├── protocol_revision
├── protocol_services_supported
├── protocol_object_types_supported
├── object_list
├── max_apdu_length_accepted
├── segmentation_supported
├── number_of_apdu_retries
├── apdu_segment_timeout
├── apdu_timeout
├── local_date
├── local_time
├── system_status
├── database_revision
├── location
├── description
├── max_master (MS/TP only)
├── max_info_frames (MS/TP only)
├── device_address_binding
├── configuration_files
├── time_synchronization_recipients
├── utc_offset
└── daylight_savings_status

Property	                    Description
object-identifier	            This uniquely identifies the BACnet device itself and is the primary key.
object-name	                    A human-readable name for the device.
object-type	                    Always "device" since this table is specifically for devices.
vendor-name	                    The name of the device manufacturer.
vendor-identifier	            A numerical code to identify the vendor.
model-name	                    The specific model of the device.
firmware-revision	            The version of the device's firmware.
application-software-version    The version of the application software running on the device.
protocol-revision	            The version of the BACnet protocol supported by the device.
protocol-services-supported	    An array of the BACnet services supported by the device.
protocol-object-types-supported	An array of the BACnet object types supported by the device.
object-list	                    A JSONB array listing the object identifiers of all objects present on the device.
max-apdu-length-accepted	    The maximum APDU size the device accepts.
segmentation-supported	        Whether the device supports BACnet segmentation (larger messages).
number-of-apdu-retries	        Number of APDU transmission retries.
apdu-segment-timeout	        Timeout (in ms) for a segment of a segmented APDU.
apdu-timeout	                Timeout (in ms) for a response to an APDU.
local-date, local-time	        Current date and time on the device.
system-status	                Operational status of the device.
database-revision	            A counter that increments with changes to the device's object database.
location	                    Physical location of the device (if available).
description	                    Detailed description of the device (if available).
max-master	                    Maximum number of masters on an MS/TP network (relevant for MS/TP devices only).
max-info-frames	                Maximum number of information frames for an MS/TP device (relevant for MS/TP devices only).
device-address-binding	        List of bindings between this device and others.
configuration-files	            List of configuration files on the device (if available).
time-synchronization-recipients	List of devices to which the device can send time sync requests.
utc-offset	                    Device's time offset from UTC.
daylight-savings-status	        Indicates if the device is observing daylight saving time.
